        "text_bEeNdX": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Way to use it with food",
            "answer": "<ul><li>Honey-infused tea (ginger, herbal or chamomile).</li><li>Drizzled over plain oatmeal (balances sweetness).</li><li>In small smoothies (with banana, almond milk, cinnamon, yoghurt and fruits).</li><li>With milk before sleep can help you relax and recover</li><li>Spread on bread by replacing the butter or you can mix it up with butter</li><li>Mad Honey Mocktail can be made on sparkling water with mint</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "text_gexxTU": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Way to use it in skin care",
            "answer": "<ul><li>Mad Honey benefits on face and skin gave glow and supple smooth tone</li><li>Mad honey has been used as a folk medicine for the cure of Arthritis. </li><li>Mad Honey can be used as a hydrating face mask for normal skin</li><li>Mad Honey can be used for woundcare</li></ul>"
          }
        }
