      "type": "basmil-image-text",
      "blocks": {
        "content_mRcgWJ": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What Expert Says?",
            "subtitle": "",
            "description": "<p>Experts suggest that mad honey can be an essential staple in a household that can be combined with daily routines and activities. They focus on moderation and caution while taking the honey. It is ideal to observe the body’s reaction and its onset of symptoms. Although it has plenty of health benefits, it’s also equally necessary to shed light on its side effects. </p><p>Moreover, daily consumption may gradually increase the tolerance to larger doses. They suggest not to use it for children, pregnant women, and individuals with weak immune systems due to the potential risks. Experts suggest taking urgent measures like visiting a nearby hospital for dizziness or nausea. </p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "button_text_2": "",
            "button_link_2": ""
          }
        },
