          "settings": {
            "title": "Safety &amp; Concerns",
            "subtitle": "",
            "description": "<p>If you're new to mad honey, begin with a small amount to assess your tolerance. This helps prevent potential overdoses or severe reactions. Stick to <a href=\"/blogs/mad-honey/effects-benefits-dose\" title=\"Effects and benefits\">recommended dosages</a>, if provided, and avoid exceeding them. Overconsumption can lead to serious health risks.</p><p>If you have any underlying health conditions or take medications, speak with a healthcare professional before using mad honey, as it may interact with certain conditions or treatments. In a worsened situation, the symptoms of dizziness, nausea, and vomiting occur. If you face any such symptoms, rush to the hospital.</p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "button_text_2": "",
            "button_link_2": ""
          }
        }
